This documentation describes accessing and configuring the Single Sign-On service.

The Single Sign-On service enables Pivotal Web Services users to authenticate with an external identity provider rather than having to create a new account or re-enter credentials. Single Sign-On grants users centralized access to applications in various spaces.

The Single Sign-On service also lets administrators use an external identity provider to manage all user access.

<p class="note"><strong>Note</strong>: This service is only available to users of Pivotal Web Services with <a href="http://pivotal.io/support/offerings">Enterprise support</a>.</p>

